The paper focuses on solving the textbook question answering task by extracting knowledge features from long text lessons and merging them with visual features, which suggests a strong emphasis on natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV). The proposed algorithm also utilizes graph convolutional networks (GCN), which is a popular technique in machine learning and falls under the category of artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper introduces a novel self-supervised open-set learning process, which involves learning without any annotations, indicating a possible connection to information retrieval (IR) and unsupervised learning (cs.IR).
